"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The np.sinc function does not return 1 for input 0 and 0 for input 1. The np.sinc function returns sin(pi*x)/(pi*x) at x=0 it is defined to be 1, but at x=1 it is sin(pi)/(pi) which is close to zero but not exactly zero due to floating point precision.\",\n  \"patch\": \"7,8c7,8\\n< assert sinc_result[0] == 1, \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n< assert sinc_result[1] == 0, \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\\n---\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[0], 1), \\\"Results not equal to one\\\"\\n> assert np.isclose(sinc_result[1], 0), \\\"Results not equal to zero\\\"\"\n}"